This pyramid has volume $\frac{1}{3} \cdot \frac{1}{2} \cdot 1 = \frac{1}{6},$ so the remaining volume is $1 - \frac{1}{6} = \frac{5}{6}.$

Since we are only looking at one octant, the total volume of the region is $8 \cdot \frac{5}{6} = \boxed{\frac{20}{3}}.$ The answer is \frac{20}{3}.

