This gives us the equation
\[\left( \begin{pmatrix} 2 + 7t \\ -3 + 5t \\ -3 - t \end{pmatrix} - \begin{pmatrix} 4 \\ 4 \\ 5 \end{pmatrix} \right) \cdot \begin{pmatrix} 7 \\ 5 \\ -1 \end{pmatrix} = 0.\]Then
\[\begin{pmatrix} -2 + 7t \\ -7 + 5t \\ -8 - t \end{pmatrix} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} 7 \\ 5 \\ -1 \end{pmatrix} = 0,\]so $(-2 + 7t) \cdot 7 + (-7 + 5t) \cdot 5 + (-8 - t) \cdot (-1) = 0$.  Solving for $t$, we find $t = \boxed{\frac{41}{75}}.$ The answer is \frac{41}{75}.

